abstract: The president goes to Orlando, the former vice president invokes two segregationist senators and Elizabeth Warren says she’ll ban private prisons.
snippet: The president goes to Orlando, the former vice president invokes two segregationist senators and Elizabeth Warren says she’ll ban private prisons.
lead_paragraph: We’re trying something new in our 2020 presidential campaign coverage.

abstract: Suddenly, Franklin D. Roosevelt is all the rage. But many Democrats don’t understand what his legacy means.
snippet: Suddenly, Franklin D. Roosevelt is all the rage. But many Democrats don’t understand what his legacy means.
lead_paragraph: Some political ideas are so old they feel new. In his 1944 State of the Union address, an ailing Franklin D. Roosevelt sketched his ambitions for a “Second Bill of Rights” — a vision of “adequate medical care,” “a good education,” “a useful and remunerative job,” “a decent home” and “freedom from unfair competition and monopolies” as the birthright of all Americans.

snippet: We tracked down 2020 Democrats and asked them the same 18 questions on health care, immigration, personal wealth and more.
lead_paragraph: We spent hours interviewing the enormous Democratic presidential field on subjects ranging from climate change and border control to fast food and personal humiliation.
